yScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   LVL 44  And broke</span><hr size=1> I am lvl 44 and broke im not twinked (under 200 int with KEI =( ) I need a place i can get PP or good int itmes. XP is a + but not needed and RM is not a place i like <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanaripethugger>Yanari Pethugger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 7:41:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Tower of Frozen Shadows</span><hr size=1> Be in a group - obtain keys, get alright exp, and maybe a Sorcerous Bowl (dunno stats, but it's pretty neat apart from the -CHA stat on it).<br>
<br>
There's more +INT and other +stats items, maybe low-level items for some, but they always sell for around 100pp in Bazaar...  <br>
Just go Zombie Trader Mode for a week with the stuff ya can loot...<br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger,<br>
Gnome - not a snack <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=masterscherer@themagicianstower>masterscherer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 6:54:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LVL 44  And broke</span><hr size=1> Gornit in OOT.  Spawn time 6 min, loot range from 4pp(least i looted) to abour 44pp (most i ever got).  There is a full section posted earlier on the board about this guy.  You can also camp the great Oowamp(sp) in timm deep, drops some decent loot...ie batskull earings.  <br>
<br>
Rytor<br>
44 Gnome Mage<br>
Vazaelle server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sscale>Sscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#333333>(11/24/02 9:15:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>    Re: LVL 44 And broke</span><hr size=1> Bloodgills are great exp and give decent loot, they drop 4pp on average and some gems and jewelry.<br>
You will be 49 before you know it and then you can do Seafuries, the best cash i had so far, i hate RM too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nimmamen>Nimmamen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/03 3:41:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: LVL 44 And broke</span><hr size=1> 49 to do seafurys my ass... get a focused 44 fire, give him all the ac and hp stuff you can (bracers and foci and stuff) and pull to the south part of sf island.  thats by gornit spawn and the pirates.  chain cast heals as needed and let the pet damage shield take them down. im guessing 1.3%xp at 44 per kill.  Uncommon (1 in 5 ?) are gems or other vendor trash that sells 30-80pp each.  Im 1.5kpp a level here.  i was once like you but now my int is about 210 w/o kei thx to a single lvl of seafurys. @_@ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kpm2k>kpm2k</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.faceoff.com/media/pics/200211063895673-F.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 2:21:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: LVL 44 And broke</span><hr size=1> Seafurys your ass?  does that mean to do them or is there something else to kill there?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ahmish>Ahmish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 6:31:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Acryllia</span><hr size=1> Hunt Tribals in DS and sell the acryllia in the Bazaar.  I average about 2k of acryllia in about 6 hours of farming. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 9:19:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Acryllia</span><hr size=1> I think that the point is ... from about 44 on being poor is a personal choice.  You have lots of places you can farm for cash if you choose to spend the time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 5:50:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pelts</span><hr size=1> Another half-decent option might be greyhopper hides from Marus Seru; my Necro was farming them for tailoring practice at 44, and most would drop either a greyhopper hide or low quality hide, either of which should sell for a few pp in the Bazaar (or farm some spiderling silks, raise your tailoring and turn the LQ hides into leather padding at 20pp a piece). The Necro pet could kill them faster than I could find them, so a Mage pet should have no problems.<br>
<br>
Also, with care you should be able to kill shadowed men as long as you can pull them far enough away from the spawn that any clerics can't heal them... they'll be well green by 44, but heals are still a pain. Essence of Shadow is a slow seller in the Bazaar, but it's a reasonably common drop (a few pieces an hour) and when it does sell I've been making 120-150pp a piece from smiths who don't want the hassle of farming it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A> at: 2/10/03 6:06:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 6:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pelts</span><hr size=1> The post above is right on the money for Marus.<br>
<br>
Make leather padding from the LQ hides, and use greyhopper hides for skillups until 95, then sell them. <br>
<br>
Details here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showMessage?topicID=442.topic">pub102.ezboard.com/fthema...=442.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Bloodgills are good.  The spears drop about 1 in 40+ kills and sell for 56pp with 130CHA.  Every hour of bloodgills was about 150pp or more, killing all 12.<br>
<br>
I keep hearing about Paineel guards.  300-500pp per hour supposedly, but you need to be amiable for a key to the city.  No matter how many frikin kobolds I slaughter, I can't seem to raise past dubious.  As a DE, you might have an easier time getting a key. <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 7:24:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Paineel</span><hr size=1> I got my Monk up from KoS to amiable so they could farm the guards, and AFAIR it took 9 or 10 hours of non-stop slaughter to get there (and I killed all the named kobolds when I saw them in case that helped). So it is possible, but it's a long slog; both Dark Elf Mage and Necro started off dubious and took several hours of killing to get to amiable too... dubious to apprehensive was the hardest part of the grind. Fortunately those two were low enough level that a lot of the time they were getting XP too, and, for the level, decent cash.<br>
<br>
Easier for a high-level pet class since it's just point-and-click slaughter with no need to chase mobs around when they run... and easier for an Evil class to raise faction as you can hand in Kobold Molars without worrying about trashing Erudin faction (forget what faction you need to do that though... think it's apprehensive). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showPrevMessage?topicID=165.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showNextMessage?topicID=165.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.threadControl?topicID=165.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=165.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=165.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="th